You should not use two different kinds of emergency contraceptive pills at the same time, or within 5 days of each other, because it may cause them not to work.', '0', 'en'), ('24645565-737f-4413-9a7e-134ac9448bba', '8048de61-64b9-4c14-b4b7-134982d999e0', '869c23a2-1994-471d-8b98-e961fd6d9fef', 'What is family planning?', 'Family planning involves thinking about and discussing if you want children, when you want them, and how many children you want.

